Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Information Services Librarian (Part-Time, Permanent) Cambridge , ON Description Posting #24-10x Information Services Librarian Part-time, Permanent Queen’s SquareIdea Exchange is a community hub comprised of the public libraries and art galleries for the City of Cambridge, a thriving city with a rich architectural heritage and the second largest community within the Waterloo Region. We are committed to supporting and inspiring our community in the exploration of reading, arts, innovation, and learning.What You’ll DoAs an Information Services Librarian, you will:Answer member questions in person, by telephone or by internet:General inquiries.Advanced catalogue search and use of available reference tools.Readers Advisory including assisting members to find resources using the library catalogue, electronic databases, microfilm equipment and the internet and making recommendations to members regarding leisure reading, viewing and listening material.Instruct members in the use of computers, maker equipment and/or software for users with all skill levels.Assist with collection management assignments as required, such as:Assists with de-selection, shelf-reading, maintenance, and cataloguing of collections as required.Coordinating specialized collections as assigned.Provides feedback on Automatic Release Plans (ARPs) for adult collections.Makes recommendations to the Manager, Queen’s Square regarding the development of adult collections’ policies and procedures.Develop guides and tutorials to instruct staff and members on the use of electronic materials, resources, and databases.Prepare bibliography reading/viewing lists and displays on selected topics for a variety of audiences.Contribute to the promotion of Idea Exchange services and collections by writing magazine articles, material reviews and website content as requested.Facilitate or conducts adult programming and group tours at the location in coordination with the Outreach and Programming Team and the Branch Manager.Responsible for addressing the conduct of members and visitors that violates Idea Exchange’s code of conduct. Acts as Person in Charge when assigned. Opens and closes building when requested and assists with monitoring building security when scheduled.Cover Member Services and Information Services duties as required.Under the direction of the Manager, Queen’s Square Adult Services, execute new initiatives and perform other duties as required.What You’ll Need to SucceedTo be qualified for and successful in the role, you should have:Required - A Masters of Library and/or Information Science (or in process) from an accredited library schoolRequired - Experience working in a library – 6 monthsRequired - Experience working in a service environment – 6 monthsAre highly-organized, and able to carry out job functions with flexibility, creativity and initiativeStrong analytical skills and a keen attention to detailExcellent multitasking skills and ability to complete responsibilities on timeExceptional verbal and written communication, critical thinking, and problem-solving skills, including the ability to explain complex technology to non-technical usersThe ability to connect with people of all ages and offer hands-on assistance.Has an inclusive and empathetic approach and a service-oriented mindsetSome working knowledge of MARC21 and current cataloguing rules and standards, such as RDA and LCSH.What We OfferWorking at Idea Exchange offers you the opportunity to be part of an organization that is welcoming, collaborative, and passionate about the community.We provide fair market compensation, consistent and reliable work schedules, paid sick time and free parking. We also offer participation in the OMERS pension plan.Pay: the range of pay is $32.50 - $39.50 per hourHours: 36.5 hours in a two-week periodSchedule: working various day, evening, and weekend shiftsWeek 1Monday OFFTuesday 9:30am - 5:30pm*Wednesday OFFThursday 1:00pm - 8:30pm**Friday OFFSaturday OFFSunday OFFWeek 2Monday OFFTuesday 9:30am - 5:30pm*Wednesday OFFThursday 1:00pm - 8:30pm**Friday OFFSaturday 12:00pm - 4:30pmSunday 1:00pm - 5:00pm* Includes a 1-hour meal break** Includes a half-hour meal breakNote: schedules are service-driven and as such are subject to change. During Sunday closures (Victoria Day to Labour Day), the schedule is reduced from 36.5 to 32.5 hours in a two-week period.How to ApplyTo be considered for the position, please apply by February 19, 2024Tell us why we should consider you for this position! Please provide both a cover letter and resume, combined as a single PDF document.Submit your application by email to recruitment@ideaexchange.orgIf applying by email, please quote “24-10x Info Librarian” in your email subject line.The anticipated start date for this position is March/April 2024.The position is open to internal and external candidates. We thank everyone for their interest, however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.Additional InformationIdea Exchange aspires to employ a staff complement that fully represents the diversity of the community we serve. All qualified individuals who would contribute to the further diversification of our organization are encouraged to apply.Idea Exchange is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to accommodating individual needs in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA). If you require any accommodations at any point during the application and hiring process, please contact Human Resources at hr@ideaexchange.org.Security Clearance Check may be required. Compensation The range of pay is $32.50 - $39.50 per hour Closes: 19 February, 2024 Idea Exchange Cambridge , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
