lan effectively. Ability to work effectively in a team environment. Knowledge of typical public library procedures and best practices. Physical Requirements: Ability to lift, carry or move library materials weighing 5 – 15 kilograms on a regular basis Ability to reach a range of shelves between 5 cm and 200 cm above floor Others: Current Criminal Record Check Current Driver’s License This position is open to candidates of all levels of experience and skill, provided that they approach the position with energy, a positive attitude, and an interest in learning. The incumbent will enjoy support from a large, professional, and experienced, management team. The Chinook Regional Library is engaged in several interesting projects, and is engaged in partnerships with many other agencies. The incumbent will have the option to participate within their aptitude and skill-set. Hours: Salary is based on an average 37.5-hour work-week. Salary: Starting at $60,000 annually, with regular increases based on skill and productivity Posted: January 15th, 2024Closing date: open until filled Please submit cover letter and resume to the address below: Jake Marion, Director Email:director@chinook.lib.sk.ca Compensation $60,000 Closes: 22 April, 2024 Chinook Regional Library Swift Current , SK Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
